issue.title: Feature request: Check for a `list` call as argument for a function that accepts any iterable
issue.body:
### Description

For example: `''.join(list(map(f, iterable)))` can be replaced by `''.join(map(f, iterable))`.

comment.body: Have you seen this pattern much? And are there other functions you'd suggest detecting this for?

issue.title: Feature request: Inverse of C417: check for `f(x) for x in iterable`
issue.body:
### Description

(Thanks for `flake8-comprehensions`, it's a good plugin)
Check for `f(x) for x in iterable` in any comprehension, and suggest replacing it with `map(f, iterable)`.
This is not objectively better like some other rules are, but IMO this is cleaner.

comment.body: Personally I find the generic syntax more readable, it means one less function the reader has to know about. So I'm not sure right now, maybe if others weigh in we could add this.

issue.title: Remove Git 2.37 workaround from install docs
issue.body:
The bug was fixed in Git 2.38, as noted on original issue: https://github.com/dandavison/delta/issues/1114#issuecomment-1265920597

I guess we can remove this from the docs now, so new users don’t switch to the old interactive `add`.

I thought of adding a section “If you’re using Git 2.37...” but that seemed too specific. If anyone encounters the error, hopefully they’ll search for it and see they need to upgrade Git.

comment.body: Thanks for the fast review. Fair enough on keeping on GitHub.
